The paper deals with the problem of finding a maximum planar subgraph of a given graph, which is a problem in graph theory and combinatorial optimization. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses approximation algorithms and implementation complexity, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper compares different algorithms and discusses their relative merits, which could make it relevant to cs.GT (Game Theory and Decision Science).
